article_id:1594,category_name:Updates,title_name:Version Update,image_path:,message:<div>Version 2.0.0 was made available for download around <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601002800"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div>To celebrate the update, a Tenfold Summon Voucher has been sent to players who started playing before <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601002800"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div>This gift can be claimed from your goodie box for up to seven days after logging in. If the gift isn&#39;t retrieved within seven days, it will be lost.</div><div><br></div><div>■Update Details</div><div><strong>・A new game mode, The Alberian Battle Royale, is here!</strong></div><div>Up to 16 players will battle for survival in this battle-royale mode. In each match of the Alberian Battle Royale, you will choose an adventurer from groups of up to nine weapon types (including the new manacaster) and upgrade them as the match progresses.</div><div><br></div><div>Adventurers who participate in the Alberian Battle Royale are not affected by dragons, weapons, wyrmprints, Halidom facilities, or the stats or effects of adventurers used during normal quests.</div><div><br></div><div>When you&#39;re just starting out, you&#39;ll be limited to choosing a sword, lance, or bow, but you can collect battle points as you play and redeem them at the treasure trade for items needed to unlock the rest. You can also redeem battle points for skins that change an adventurer&#39;s appearance and other items.</div><div><br></div><div>Show your skill with your favorite weapon type by conquering all comers to reap the rewards!</div><div><br></div><div>▼Event Duration</div><div><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601002800"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1604123999"></span></div><div><br></div><div>For details on when this event will return after it has concluded, please await a future notification.</div><div><br></div><div>▼Conditions for Participation</div><div>Any player who has completed the first tutorial summon may participate.</div><div><br></div><div>For further details, please see the following notification:</div><div><br></div><div><a href="https://dragalialost.com/en/news/detail/1624">The Alberian Battle Royale Is Now Live!</a></div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/9002fbd3dc9bc862e277ca0cdc7f46a3.png"></div><div><br></div><div><strong>・The weapon and crafting systems have been changed.</strong></div><div>The Craft and Enhance tabs have been removed and replaced by the Weapons/Crafting tab from which players can select, craft, and upgrade a weapon from various groups. A new feature called the weapon bonus has been added that can be unlocked by upgrading your collection of weapons. Certain weapon abilities will apply to all weapons of a certain type once unlocked. The way players use and upgrade weapons has changed in other ways as well.</div><div><br></div><div>Please note that certain aspects of team configurations have been reset alongside these changes.</div><div><br></div><div>For further details, please see the following notification:</div><div><br></div><div><a href="https://dragalialost.com/en/news/detail/1603">Regarding Changes to the Weapon and Crafting Systems</a></div><div><br></div><div><strong>・The wyrmprint system has been changed.</strong></div><div>In Version 1.23.1 and earlier, each wyrmprint could typically have up to two abilities, and some with certain event perks had three. In Version 2.0.0, each wyrmprint typically has one ability (not including wyrmprints with event perks, which may have two). Certain wyrmprints have an affinity, and equipping multiple wyrmprints with the same affinity will activate an affinity bonus, providing various ability effects. The UI allowing you to select and equip wyrmprints has been updated.</div><div><br></div><div>Please note that certain aspects of team configurations have been reset alongside these changes.</div><div><br></div><div>For further details, please see the following notification:</div><div><br></div><div><a href="https://dragalialost.com/en/news/detail/1605">Regarding Changes to the Wyrmprint System</a></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><strong>・The summoning system has been changed.</strong></div><div>A new item, the wyrmsigil, can be earned by summoning on certain summon showcases.</div><div><br></div><div>When summoning on eligible summon showcases, you will earn wyrmsigils equal to the number of summons performed using wyrmite, Summon Vouchers, or Tenfold Summon Vouchers and double the number of summons performed using diamantium. You will not earn wyrmsigils for summoning on certain summon showcases such as Platinum Showcases, 5★ Adventurer Summons, or 5★ Dragon Summons.</div><div><br></div><div>If you earn 300 wyrmsigils from a particular summon showcase, you can redeem them for an eligible adventurer or dragon appearing in that showcase&#39;s exchange lineup while the showcase is still active.</div><div><br></div><div>When the summon showcase ends, any wyrmsigils that were earned from it will be converted into an equal number of wyrmsigil remnants that can be redeemed for various items at the Shop&#39;s treasure trade.</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/d75973fdd27be994ab744c86fd2e1001.png"></div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/219af836dbf514945aa94671f2eddee1.png"></div><div><br></div><div><strong>・The balance of adventurers and dragons has been adjusted.</strong></div><div>The balance of certain adventurers and dragons has been adjusted to make it easier to use a greater variety of them when taking on quests. Please note that previously adjusted adventurers and dragons may have had their skills or ability effects adjusted again.</div><div><br></div><div>For further details, please see the following notification:</div><div><br></div><div><a href="https://dragalialost.com/en/news/detail/1629">Regarding Adjustments to Adventurer and Dragon Balance</a></div><div><br></div><div><strong>・The rewards and difficulty of quests played in solo play and co-op play have been adjusted.</strong></div><div>Certain Void Battles, Advanced Dragon Trials, and The Agito Uprising quests have been split into solo play and co-op play categories. The difficulty and rewards of each solo and co-op play quest have been adjusted. Some adjustments made to the difficulty of these quests were based on adjustments made to adventurer and dragon balance.</div><div><br></div><div>We plan to continue adding both solo and co-op play categories for future high-difficulty quests, including the upcoming Master difficulty for The Agito Uprising.</div><div><br></div><div>Details on upcoming quests will be provided in an upcoming notification.</div><div><br></div><div>Affected quests are listed below:</div><div><br></div><div>Void Battles:</div><div>Void Zephyr Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div>Void Poseidon Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div>Void Agni Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div>Void Jeanne d&#39;Arc Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div>Void Nidhogg Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div>Volcanic Chimera Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div>Tidal Chimera Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div>Tempest Chimera Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div>Luminous Chimera Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div>Ebon Chimera Strike: Standard/Expert</div><div><br></div><div>Advanced Dragon Trials:</div><div>High Midgardsormr&#39;s Trial: Prelude/Standard/Expert/Master</div><div>High Mercury&#39;s Trial: Prelude/Standard/Expert/Master</div><div>High Brunhilda&#39;s Trial: Prelude/Standard/Expert/Master</div><div>High Jupiter&#39;s Trial: Prelude/Standard/Expert/Master</div><div>High Zodiark&#39;s Trial: Prelude/Standard/Expert/Master</div><div><br></div><div>The Agito Uprising:</div><div>Volk&#39;s Wrath: Standard/Expert/Master</div><div>Ciella&#39;s Wrath: Standard/Expert</div><div>Ayaha &amp; Otoha&#39;s Wrath: Standard/Expert</div><div>Kai Yan&#39;s Wrath: Standard/Expert/Master</div><div>Tartarus&#39;s Wrath: Standard/Expert</div><div><br></div><div>▼Rewards</div><div>The same types of item rewards will be available from both solo and co-op play, but players will earn more rewards from co-op play. Weekly bonus rewards and the number of times that players can obtain them will be shared between solo and co-op play. The number of times that weekly bonuses for Advanced Dragon Trials and The Agito Uprising can be obtained will be set to five times per week starting at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601272800"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div>▼Endeavors</div><div>Endeavors related to the quests affected by these adjustments have been changed so they can be cleared when playing in solo play.</div><div>Notes:</div><div>・These endeavors cannot be cleared in co-op play.</div><div>・Endeavors that have already been cleared will remain cleared.</div><div><br></div><div>▼Conditions For Unlocking Quests</div><div>Certain quests that serve as a prerequisite for unlocking the quests affected by these adjustments may be cleared in either solo play or co-op play.</div><div><br></div><div>Conditions for unlocking The Agito Uprising quests are as follows:</div><div><br></div><div>・Before: clear Chapter 10 / 6-3 (Normal) of the main campaign and an Advanced Dragon Trial on Standard difficulty</div><div>・After: clear Chapter 10 / 6-3 (Normal) of the main campaign and an Advanced Dragon Trial on Standard difficulty (in either solo or co-op play)</div><div><br></div><div>The clear status of each quest before the release of Version 2.0.0 has been applied to its co-op play clear status in Version 2.0.0.</div><div><br></div><div>▼Removal of the Mentor Bonus</div><div>The Mentor Bonus has been removed alongside these changes. Endeavors related to the Mentor Bonus have been removed and the related epithets are no longer obtainable. Epithets already obtained may continue to be used.</div><div><br></div><div>Note: Any uncollected rewards for completing an endeavor related to the Mentor Bonus will no longer be obtainable after <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601100000"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/da2f40d7f6926f9308008d0ff1e9cb36.png"></div><div><strong>・A new weapon type, the manacaster, has been added.</strong></div><div>Manacasters have three modes, and the mode available for use differs from adventurer to adventurer.</div><div><br></div><div>▼Manacaster modes</div><div>Long-range mode:</div><div>Specializes in attacks from long range.</div><div>Close-range mode:</div><div>Specializes in attacks from close range.</div><div>Rapid-fire mode:</div><div>Unleashes a rapid-fire barrage with a force strike.</div><div><br></div><div>▼3★ manacaster-toting adventurer gift</div><div>To celebrate the introduction of the manacaster, all players have been gifted with the long-range attack specialist Sharpshooter Joe. Adventurers of varying manacaster modes will be added over time through summoning events and more.</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/3e35e8bc8f934f11d24c16ab635701c0.png"></div><div><br></div><div>▼Addition of manacaster-related facility and item</div><div>The following facility and item related to manacasters have been added:</div><div>・Manacaster dojo</div><div>・Manacaster tablet</div><div>Note: Manacaster tablets can be obtained from The Imperial Onslaught, the Item Summon, and other sources.</div><div><br></div><div>▼Manacaster weapon lineup</div><div>The following manacaster weapons have been implemented in the Version 2.0.0 update:</div><div><br></div><div>・Core Weapons: 4★ non-elemenal weapon, 5★ non-elemental weapon, 5★ light-attuned weapon</div><div>Note: There are no 3★ non-elemental manacasters. Players can craft a 4★ non-elemenal manacaster if their Smithy is Lv. 4 or higher.</div><div>・Void Weapons: to be added in the future</div><div>・Chimeratech Weapons: 5★ light-attuned weapon</div><div>・High Dragon Weapons: 5★ light-attuned weapon</div><div>Note: Because void manacasters cannot be crafted at this time, crafting a high dragon version will not require a void version (unlike the other weapon types). Instead, crafting a high dragon manacaster will require a fully upgraded 5★ non-elemental core manacaster and Smithy Lv. 7+.</div><div>・Agito Weapons: 6★ light-attuned weapon</div><div>・Other: Battleworn Manacaster (1★ non-elemenal weapon)</div><div><br></div><div>Additional manacaster weapons will be added in the future.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>・The game visuals have been overhauled.</strong></div><div>With this fresh look for adventurers and dragons, their 3D models are even closer to their illustrations.</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/d7515fcc7d5db158b3e3d20410c5f4e7.png"></div><div><br></div><div><strong>・A skip feature has been added to the main campaign.</strong></div><div>If a player has yet to clear chapter 10 / 6-3 (Normal) of the main campaign, they can use the skip feature on the quest selection screen in chapters 1 through 10 to clear all main campaign quests on normal up to and including chapter 10.</div><div><br></div><div>Players will obtain the first clear rewards and quest endeavor rewards for all quests cleared using this feature. Their player level will be increased to 60 and certain facilities in the Halidom will be constructed. Facility levels will be raised as follows:</div><div><br></div><div>The Halidom: Lv. 6</div><div>Smithy: Lv. 6</div><div>Rupie Mine (4 total): Lv. 15</div><div>Dragontree: Lv. 15</div><div>Altar of each element (2 each): Lv. 10</div><div>Dojo of each weapon (2 each): Lv. 10</div><div><br></div><div>Notes:</div><div>・If a player clears chapter 10 / 6-3 (Normal) of the main campaign without using the skip feature after it has been implemented, they will receive the materials required to level the facilities specified above and 350 hustle hammers as well as the experience required to increase their player level from 1 to 60 as a reward for clearing chapter 10.</div><div>・Players who have already cleared chapter 10 / 6-3 (Normal) of the main campaign when this feature is implemented will receive the materials required to level the facilities specified above and 350 hustle hammers as well as 100 quality honey and 35 blessed ethon ashes as a reward for clearing chapter 10.</div><div>・Players can learn what happened in the stories they skipped by reading Notte&#39;s Super Rad Plot Synopsis, which is accessible from the Menu button on the top right of the Home screen.</div><div><br></div><div>Notte&#39;s Super Rad Plot Synopsis will cover events up to chapter 2 of the main campaign starting at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601002800"></span>. Future chapters will be added over time.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>・The Crafting Pack has been added to Starter Packs.</strong></div><div><strong><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/b5848c27538d2903e75d8a0845618144.png"></strong><br></div><div>The Crafting Pack was added to Starter Packs in the in-game Shop at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601002800"></span>. This pack includes diamantium and special endeavors. You can earn rewards by completing endeavors related to weapon crafting.</div><div><br></div><div>Notes:</div><div>・Endeavor rewards can be obtained even if the endeavor was completed before the pack was purchased.</div><div>・This product is not available in some countries/regions.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>・A menu with options to reduce the app&#39;s size has been added.</strong></div><div>The Reduce Application Size menu has been added to the Help section on the Title screen. You can freely choose to enable or disable multiple options from three different groups.</div><div>Note: Deleting downloaded data will result in the app taking less space on your device, but this data will need to be re-downloaded if an option that requires it is enabled.</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/a1fed99bee7f26c5cfdb32ecbbde2c72.png"></div><div><br></div><div>■Changes to Event Compendium rewards</div><div>Alongside changes to the weapon, crafting, and wyrmprint systems, certain Event Compendium endeavors, treasure trade rewards, and cumulative event point rewards have been changed as follows:</div><div><br></div><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="margin-right: calc(8% - 0px); width: 92%;" width="952"><tbody><tr height="24"><td height="24" width="212">Event<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%;" width="207">Endeavors<br></td><td style="width: 30.4174%;" width="334">Details<br></td><td style="width: 32.4391%;" width="199">Reward</td></tr><tr height="24;"><td style="height: 24; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Flames of Reflection<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">added<br></td><td style="width: 30.4174%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Defeat the Troll Smith Twice</td><td style="width: 32.4391%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Dragon Smiths wyrmprint<br></td></tr><tr height="24"><td style="height: 24; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Miracle of Dragonyule<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">added<br></td><td style="width: 30.4174%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Defeat the Festive Treant<br></td><td style="width: 32.4391%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Ringing Wand weapon skin &times; 1<br></td></tr><tr height="24"><td style="height: 24; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Miracle of Dragonyule<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">added<br></td><td style="width: 30.4174%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Defeat the Festive Treant Two Times<br></td><td style="width: 32.4391%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A Slice of Dragonyule wyrmprint<br></td></tr><tr height="24"><td style="height: 24; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Miracle of Dragonyule<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">added<br></td><td style="width: 30.4174%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Defeat the Festive Treant Three Times<br></td><td style="width: 32.4391%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Wishing Knife weapon skin &times; 1<br></td></tr><tr height="24"><td style="height: 24; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Miracle of Dragonyule<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">removed<br></td><td style="width: 30.4174%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Collect 100 Holiday Cheer in One Go<br></td><td style="width: 32.4391%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Ringing Wand weapon &times; 5<br></td></tr><tr height="24"><td style="height: 24; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Miracle of Dragonyule<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">removed<br></td><td style="width: 30.4174%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Clear Three Challenge Battles<br></td><td style="width: 32.4391%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Wishing Knife weapon &times; 5<br></td></tr><tr height="24"><td style="height: 24; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A Wish to the Winds<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">added&nbsp;</td><td style="width: 30.4174%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Defeat the Water Troll King Twice<br></td><td style="width: 32.4391%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Louise&#39;s Hobbies wyrmprint<br></td></tr><tr height="24"><td style="height: 24; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dream Big Under the Big Top<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">added<br></td><td style="width: 30.4174%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Defeat the Manticore Twice<br></td><td style="width: 32.4391%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Astounding Trick wyrmprint<br></td></tr><tr height="24"><td style="height: 24; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Hunt for Harmony<br></td><td style="width: 11.7539%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">added<br></td><td style="width: 30.4174%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Defeat the Volcanic Cyclops Twice<br></td><td style="width: 32.4391%; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A Mother&#39;s Love wyrmprint<br></td></tr></tbody></table><div><br></div><div>・Treasure trade rewards</div><div>For all Event Compendium events, wyrmprints are no longer exchangeable.</div><div><br></div><div>・Cumulative event point rewards</div><div>For all Event Compendium events, wyrmprints available as rewards have been changed to 300 eldwater.</div><div><br></div><div>・Regrading the 5★ wyrmprint The Greatest Gift</div><div>The 5★ wyrmprint The Greatest Gift, meant to be obtained after reading episode 5 of The Miracle of Dragonyule event in the Event Compendium, is temporarily unobtainable. This issue will be addressed in a future update. Thank you for your patience and understanding.</div><div><br></div><div>■Other Changes</div><div>・The title screen will display a 2nd anniversary illustration after the Verison 2.0.0 update is released until <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1603087199"></span>.</div><div>・2nd anniversary stickers will be added at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601186400"></span>.</div><div>・2nd anniversary voice lines will be available from <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601186400"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1603087199"></span>. To listen to them, tap or press and hold an adventurer on the Adventurers screen or the Edit Team screen, then tap the magnifying glass icon in the bottom right corner of the screen. You will be able to listen to the voice lines on the screen that opens.</div><div>・A 2nd anniversary background music track, &quot;a n n i v e r s a r y,&quot; will be available from <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601186400"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1603087199"></span> in the System tab under Options on the Menu.</div><div>・The amount of astral shards necessary to exchange for items in the treasure trade for Astral Raids has been adjusted. Additions to the treasure trade item lineup will be made at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1601532000"></span>.</div><div>・The setting that hides the effects of actions (attacking, using skills, using force strikes, etc.) not performed by the controlled adventurer that is enabled by selecting Basic in Graphic Settings in Options has been made available at settings other than Basic.</div><div><br></div><div>■Issues Addressed</div><div>・When the adventurer Gala Alex shapeshifts into the dragon Ramiel and uses the ability Angelic Declaration, the effect that immediately readies the user&#39;s second skill for use is not applied to the skill gauge.</div><div>・If the adventurer Albert&#39;s Impulse Slash ability is unlocked, under certain conditions even if he is not electrified, the skill gauge does not always deplete when he uses force strikes.</div><div>・In Ayaha &amp; Otoha&#39;s Wrath on Standard and Expert difficulties, when either Ayaha or Otoha, but not both, is in the area of effect for a debuff zone placed by the player, the debuff zone does not always affect Ayaha &amp; Otoha (human form).</div><div>・When the Burning Ambition buff applied by the adventurer Nobunaga&#39;s Dream Offensive skill ends, it may damage enemies even if they are in an invincible state.</div><div><br></div><div>■Notes</div><div>1. It may take time for the store to reflect the updated information. Players may not be able to perform updates due to their device&#39;s data cache being full. If you are unable to perform the update, restart your device, then try downloading it from the store.</div><div>2. Any adventurers and game screenshots shown are still in development.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div>,start_time:1601002800,update_time1601028106